class QgsMessageOutput
{
%Docstring(signature="appended")
Interface for showing messages from QGIS in GUI independent way.

This class provides abstraction of a dialog for showing output to the user.
By default :py:class:`QgsMessageConsoleOutput` will be used if not overridden with other
message output creator function.

QGIS application uses :py:class:`QgsMessageView` class for displaying a dialog to the user.

Object deletes itself when it's not needed anymore. Children should use
signal :py:func:`~destroyed` to notify the deletion
%End

